      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall shear stress distribution — qualitative variability assessment",
      "description": "Wall shear stress spatial distributions compared against PIV-derived experimental measurements at the pump outlet. Agreement assessed as acceptable across 4 of 5 operating points. Inherent variability in experimental PIV measurements assessed qualitatively by the engineering team based on known sensor noise characteristics and fluid seeding density variation; no structured uncertainty quantification node was linked to this result. The qualitative assessment noted cycle-to-cycle variability of approximately 8–12% in measured WSS but this was not propagated through a formal UQ framework."
