    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cou2-vad-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-lead",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted as documented. All 13 credibility factors have been evaluated; 7 factors assessed with achieved levels below required levels, 6 factors flagged as not-assessed epistemic gaps at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was applied to boundary condition inputs and hemolysis index predictions. Wall shear stress variability was assessed qualitatively by the engineering team based on known sensor characteristics, with inherent variability noted but not propagated through a formal structured UQ framework. The overall credibility package is accepted as a complete record of the current state of evidence, with the understanding that the Not Accepted decision on model use reflects the identified gaps.",
